	(text "*NOTE:\n------\nThe battery can only be charged when the power switch is closed, \nbecause the 'B+'' circuit is disconnected when 'SW1' is open. \n\nThis is not a design flaw, but it's important to remember: \nyou'll need to charge the device while it's powered on. \nIf desired, this can easily be changed by moving the switch \nto the 'B-' break or by using a separate switch on an 'n-channel MOSFET'."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
